    dc:creator "Amaral, Edna Maria", "Fachin, Diego Aguilar", "Falaschi, Rafaela Lopes" ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "Puparium of Merosargus cingulatus Schiner, 1868 and Ptecticus lanei James, 1941 (Diptera: Stratiomyidae: Sarginae), with new geographical records for the species and a list of all known immatures of the subfamily" ;
    bibo:endPage "440" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2024-02-07" ;
    bibo:startPage "421" ;
    bibo:volume "5406" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628052>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628056>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628058>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628060>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628068> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628052>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Merosargus cingulatus Schiner, 1868. 1–2. Habitus, dorsal view, male and female, respectively. 3. Habitus, lateral view, male, arrow indicates prothorax. 4–5. Head, dorsal and frontal views, respectively, arrow indicates frontal callus on the lower frons." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10628052/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628056>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12–15. Puparium of Merosargus cingulatus, illustration based on images. 12, 14. Head and prothorax, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. 13, 15. Meso- and metathorax and abdominal segments, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Abbreviations: 1–8, abdominal segments; I, prothorax; II, mesothorax; III, metathorax; ant, antenna; abd spr, abdominal spiracle; Ad, anterodorsal setae; Ap, apical setae; asl, anal slit; Cf, clypeofrontal setae; D, dorsal setae; Dl, dorsolateral setae; e, eye; L, lateral setae; lb, labrum; Lb, labral setae; mo, molar area; mx plp, maxillary palpus; p spr, posterior spiracle; prth spr, prothoracic spiracle; Sa, subapical setae; sp, sternal patch; V, ventral setae; Va, ventroapical setae; Vl, ventrolateral setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10628056/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628058>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–20. Puparium of Merosargus cingulatus. 16, 17. Head, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. 18. Head and prothorax, lateral view. 19. Abdominal segments 6 to 8, ventral view. 20. Detail of the sternal patch, abdominal segment 6, ventral view. Black arrow points to lateral prominence of the head. Abbreviations: ant, antenna; asl, anal slit; Cf, clypeofrontal setae; Dl, dorsolateral setae; e, eye; L, lateral setae; Lb, labral setae; mo, molar area; mx plp, maxillary palpus; prth spr, prothoracic spiracle; sp, sternal patch; V, ventral setae; Va, ventroapical setae; Vl, ventrolateral setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10628058/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628060>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–27. SEM images of puparium of Merosargus cingulatus. 21. Detail of the head, ventral view. 22. Antenna. 23, 25. Detail of the sternal patch. 24. Abdominal segments 5 to 8, ventral view. 26–27. Detail of the tegument of segment 6. Abbreviations: ant, antenna;Ap, apical setae; asl, anal slit; L, lateral setae; Lb, labral setae; Sa, subapical setae; sp, sternal patch; V, ventral setae; Va, ventroapical setae; Vl, ventrolateral setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10628060/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10628068>
    dc:description "FIGURE 43. Geographic distribution of Merosargus cingulatus. FIGURE 44. Geographic distribution of Ptecticus lanei." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10628068/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

